4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT LOWERING SCHOOL DISTRICT PROPERTY TAXES FOR
5 TRANSPORTATION BY INCREASING THE ON-SCHEDULE REIMBURSEMENT RATES; AMENDING
6 SECTION 20-10-141, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 20-10-141, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "20-10-141. Schedule of maximum reimbursement by mileage rates. (1) (a) The mileage rates in
12 subsection (2) for school transportation constitute the maximum reimbursement to districts for school
13 transportation from state and county sources of transportation revenue under the provisions of 20-10-145 and
14 20-10-146. These rates may not limit the amount that a district may budget in its transportation fund budget in
15 order to provide for the estimated and necessary cost of school transportation during the ensuing school fiscal
16 year.
17 (b) All bus miles traveled on bus routes approved by the county transportation committee are
18 reimbursable.
19 (c) Nonbus mileage is reimbursable for a vehicle driven by a bus driver to and from an overnight
20 location of a school bus when the location is more than 10 miles from the school.
21 (d) A district may approve additional bus or nonbus miles within its own district or approved service
22 area but may not claim reimbursement for the mileage.
23 (e) Any vehicle, the operation of which is reimbursed for bus mileage under the rate provisions of
24 this schedule, must be a school bus, as defined by this title, driven by a qualified driver on a bus route approved
25 by the county transportation committee and the superintendent of public instruction.
26 (2) (a) The rate for each bus mile traveled must be determined in accordance with the following
27 schedule:
28 (i) 50 85 cents for a school bus as defined in 20-10-101(5)(a)(ii);
