1 (ii) 95 cents $1.58 for a school bus with a rated capacity of not more than 49 passenger seating
2 positions;
3 (iii) $1.15 $1.91 for a school bus with a rated capacity of 50 to 59 passenger seating positions;
4 (iv) $1.36 $2.26 for a school bus with a rated capacity of 60 to 69 passenger seating positions;
5 (v) $1.57 $2.61 for a school bus with a rated capacity of 70 to 79 passenger seating positions; and
6 (vi) $1.80 $2.99 for a school bus with 80 or more passenger seating positions.
7 (b) Nonbus mileage, as provided in subsection (1), must be reimbursed at a rate of 50 85 cents a
8 mile.
9 (3) The rated capacity is the number of passenger seating positions of a school bus as determined
10 under the policy adopted by the board of public education. If modification of a school bus to accommodate
11 pupils with disabilities reduces the rated capacity of the bus, the reimbursement to a district for pupil
12 transportation is based on the rated capacity of the bus prior to modification.
13 (4) The number of pupils riding the school bus may not exceed the passenger seating positions of
14 the bus."
15
16 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Applicability. [This act] applies to on-schedule reimbursements
19 supporting school district transportation budgets in school fiscal years beginning on or after July 1, 2025.
